criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  age over 18 years;

          -  have had surgery to treat breast cancer;- have completed chemotherapy and / or
             radiotherapy;

          -  have upper quadrant pain homolateral to surgery for at least the last 3 months, with a
             score of 4 or more on the visual analog scale (VAS) in the last week

          -  present a score greater than or equal to 30 on the Arm, Shoulder, and Hand Dysfunction
             Questionnaire (DASH).

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  difficulty in understanding the Portuguese language to answer the questionnaires;

          -  have had bilateral surgery to treat breast cancer;

          -  be in palliative care;

          -  pregnant women;

          -  be using analgesic and / or anti-inflammatory drugs

          -  women with rheumatic diseases

          -  be in physical therapy during the intervention period.
